title: Appointment to Hospital Authority
content_text:
p>
			The Government announced today (July 26) the appointment of 
			Professor Gabriel Matthew Leung to the Hospital Authority for two 
			years with effect from August 1, 2013. Following is a brief biography of Professor Leung: Professor Gabriel Matthew Leung is Dean-Designate of the Li Ka Shing 
			Faculty of Medicine, the University of Hong Kong. He will take 
			office on August 1, 2013. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, welcomed

Professor Leung to the Hospital Authority. He also thanked Professor Lee Sum-ping, who will retire from the Hospital Authority with effect from August 1, 2013, for his advice and contribution to the Hospital Authority over the years. The Hospital Authority, as from August 1, 2013, will comprise a chairman, 23 non-official members, three public officers and one principal officer from the Hospital Authority.
